WEBVTT

00:13:28.553 --> 00:13:30.664
that happens to support our viewpoint --

00:13:30.688 --> 00:13:32.791
that would, again, be confirmation bias.

00:13:32.815 --> 00:13:35.370
Nor does it mean
that if seven studies show A

00:13:35.394 --> 00:13:37.062
and three show B,

00:13:37.086 --> 00:13:38.569
that A must be true.

00:13:39.109 --> 00:13:41.768
What matters is the quality,

00:13:41.792 --> 00:13:44.609
and not the quantity of expertise.

00:13:45.879 --> 00:13:47.679
So we should do two things.

00:13:48.434 --> 00:13:53.012
First, we should critically examine
the credentials of the authors.

00:13:53.807 --> 00:13:57.950
Just like you'd critically examine
the credentials of a potential surgeon.

00:13:58.347 --> 00:14:01.553
Are they truly experts in the matter,